  "name": "posterior communicating artery",
  "description": "The posterior communicating artery is a vessel of the Circle of Willis that connects the internal carotid artery to the posterior cerebral artery. The original phrasing provided was 'posterior communicating arteries' (plural), illustrating the same anatomical structure in plural form.",
